description._content: Catalog #: 09_01179 Title: H. Murray Gibson Special Collection Photo La Crosse Wisconsin Date: Circa 1920s Additional Information: members of flying club of la Crosse, Wisconsin, including instructor barney Root (kneeling in front of propellor) and H. Murray Gibson (5th from right), H. Murray Gibson was a bus driver for the Greyhound bus company. He was also an aviation enthusiast who took flying lessons throughout the 1930s.
